 sauce"]},{"title":"Rice and Broccoli","content":["1000 g water","1 ½ tsp fine sea salt","300 g white long grain rice","350 g broccoli florets (approx. 1 head)"]},{"title":"Tofu","content":["vegetable oil, for frying","400 g firm tofu, pressed for 30 minutes (see tip) then diced (2 cm)","sesame seeds, for garnishing","2 spring onions, thinly sliced (5 mm), for garnishing"]}],"id":"r402828","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-ZLIncQ2wsbo\/XZVRrKK13FI\/AAAAAAAAdRg\/QQ5K9SPHA-0wXh9Pq6Fk0NwuZK6rCXEbQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_tlDtWq7GFuFtWXGk.png","title":"Crispy Korean Tofu","publishedAt":"2018-11-12T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"30 g","fat":"24 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"135 g","calories":"3791 kJ \/ 900 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, large saucepan, large plate, paper towels, food thermometer, hob","hintsAndTricks":["To press tofu: Place <b>2-3 sheets<b> paper towels on a large plate or baking tray then place block of tofu on top. Place another <b>2-3 sheets<b> paper towels on top of tofu, then place another plate or baking tray on top. Top with <b>2-3 heavy<b> books and leave for at least <b>30 minutes<b> before continuing with recipe."],"basicInfo":["medium","40m","1h 20m","4 portions"]}